// E2E tests for the `:flush`, `:flush <selector>`, `:changes`, and `:dirty`
// REPL meta-commands (ADR 0082 Phase 3, BT-2287).
//
// These CLI-side aliases desugar to the Beamtalk expressions:
//   :flush          → Workspace flush
//   :flush <sel>    → Workspace flush: <sel>
//   :changes        → Workspace changes
//   :dirty          → Workspace changes notEmpty
//
// The tests verify the aliases dispatch through to the underlying message
// sends. Runtime semantics of those calls are covered separately:
// workspace_changes.btscript (BT-2284) for `Workspace changes`; the
// `beamtalk_workspace_flush_tests` EUnit suite (BT-2286) for `Workspace flush`.
//
// IMPORTANT: meta-commands are dispatched by the REPL/test harness *only when
// the entire line is* `:flush`, `:changes`, `:dirty`, or `:flush <selector>`.
// They are NOT composable inside larger expressions — assertions about return
// shape route through the underlying message-send form on a separate line.
//
// IMPORTANT: REPL-protocol cases share one long-lived workspace session. Live
// patches from earlier cases (e.g. `Counter >> increment => ...` from
// compile_source_patch.btscript) accumulate as non-flushable ChangeLog entries
// (no active project tree → all sourceFile paths classify as "dependency"),
// so the active changeset is generally non-empty here. The assertions below
// compare alias-vs-direct return shapes, not exact dirty-state values.

// ===========================================================================
// :dirty — alias for `Workspace changes notEmpty`.
// ===========================================================================

// The underlying expression returns a Boolean.
(Workspace changes notEmpty) isKindOf: Boolean
// => true

// The alias dispatches successfully (wildcard: meta-commands aren't
// composable, so we can only verify the call doesn't raise an error).
:dirty
// => _

// ===========================================================================
// :changes — alias for `Workspace changes`
// ===========================================================================

// :changes returns a value (wildcard — the harness can't introspect it
// directly because meta-commands aren't composable inside expressions).
:changes
// => _

// The underlying call returns a ChangeLog. Both calls go through the same
// FFI singleton, so the dispatch path is exercised by both.
Workspace changes isKindOf: ChangeLog
// => true

// ===========================================================================
// :flush — alias for `Workspace flush`
// ===========================================================================

// :flush returns a FlushResult value (wildcard — exact contents depend on
// what was pending from earlier cases).
:flush
// => _

// ===========================================================================
// :flush <selector> — alias for `Workspace flush: <selector>`
// ===========================================================================

// :flush with a Class selector dispatches as `Workspace flush: Object`.
// `Object` typically has no pending entries, so the call is a no-op.
:flush Object
// => _

// :flush with a Symbol kind selector dispatches as `Workspace flush: #'new-class'`.
:flush #'new-class'
// => _

// :flush with a Dictionary `#{ #file => path }` selector dispatches as
// `Workspace flush: #{ #file => "..." }`.
:flush #{ #file => "src/never_dirty.bt" }
// => _

// After all the targeted flushes, the ChangeLog is still queryable.
:changes
// => _
